So, this is the result of our first participation in the Ludum Dare game jam. The game is a shooter with microscopic evolution of single-celled creatures, called allels, or something. We liked the final result because the gameplay was very fun and frenetic, and the theme "evolution" was very present: evolve to survive. The survival of their species depends on how much you evolve. It was a fun work made by just two guys, that's it.

To play Allel, use WASD to control the character and shoot everything that moves using the mouse button.

